<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0363</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Drop Heavy Rain on Texas</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms covered much of the Texas coast today
after dropping heavy rain over the region.
   The storms Wednesday evening produced flooding in some cities.
In six hours overnight, heavier rainfall included more than 3
inches at Beeville and 2\ inches at Corpus Christi.
   Widely scattered showers and thunderstorms dampened the middle
Mississippi Valley, isolated showers fell over the northern and
central Plains, and light rain and drizzle lingered over eastern
Maine. Fair skies prevailed across the rest of the nation.
   Today's forecast called for showers and a few thunderstorms
scattered across the upper and eastern Great Lakes, and scattered
showers and thunderstorms over the western and central Gulf Coast.
The rest of the nation was expected to have mostly sunny skies.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 70s or 80s across
much of the nation; 60s from the upper Mississippi Valley and the
northern half of the Great Lakes into New England; 50s over Upper
Michigan and northern Maine; 90s in California's central and
southern valleys, and in inland sections of southern Texas; and 100
to 110 degrees from southern Nevada to the desert Southwest.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 31
degrees at Marquette, Mich., to 85 at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 62 fair; Boston 52 fair; Buffalo 46 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 62 foggy; Cincinnati 49 fair; Cleveland 48 fair;
Detroit 50 fair; Miami 72 fair; New York 53 fair; Philadelphia 53
partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 40 fair; Portland, Maine, 48 fair;
Washington 54 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 57 partly cloudy; Chicago 60 cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 67 partly cloudy; Denver 50 fair; Des Moines 61
fair; Indianapolis 54 fair; Kansas City 60 fair; Minneapolis-St.
Paul 48 fair; Nashville 51 fair; New Orleans 68 fair; St. Louis 67
partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 58 fair; Anchorage 48 partly cloudy; Las
Vegas 72 fair; Los Angeles 63 fair; Phoenix 81 fair; Salt Lake City
53 fair; San Diego 63 fair; San Francisco 53 fair; Seattle 61 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 41 fair; Toronto 39 fair.
</TEXT>
