<HEAD>Carson's Reagan-Astrology Quips</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Carson-Returns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some of the jokes involving the
reports of astrology in the White House that host Johnny Carson
featured in his return to the ``Tonight Show.''
   _I am not an expert on astrology, I know a little bit about it,
but I understand the horoscope with the chart as they call it is
divided into the so-called 12 houses, and I just didn't know the
White House was one of them.
   _We apparently have a new cabinet officer in the government I
was not aware of _ the Secretary of Health, Education and
Soothsaying.
   _Apparently the astrologist says that Reagan's sign is the
rising house of Aquarius. Nancy's house is, I think, in the house
of (dress designer) Adolfo. I could be wrong, it could be Bill
Blass, but I think that's close.
   _Do you get the feeling if this gets out of hand the National
Security Council will be sitting around a table with a pack of
tarot cards planning the nation's defense? `Gee, a black queen,
Frank, launch the missiles.'
   _Reagan performs at his best during a full moon. ... Big deal,
so does the Wolfman.
   Carson also noted that Reagan has said he never made a policy
decision based on astrology. Why? ``Well (imitating the president's
voice), because that little pointer on my Ouija board moved to
`No.'''
