<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Police Say Actor Rose Was Murdered; Cocaine Found</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with charges, identities of three
of the suspects. ADDS background. No pickup.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By RUDDY GONZALEZ</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said today
American actor George Rose was clubbed to death by his 18-year-old
adopted son and three other men this month and that cocaine was
found on his body.
   Police spokesman Col. Aquiles Pimentel Cruz said at a news
conference that the four men were charged with murder in the
68-year-old Rose's death. He presented three of them to reporters
and said the fourth had not been arrested.
   Pimentel Cruz did not say how much of the drug was found on
Rose's body.
   The three suspects told reporters they had killed Rose, who was
found dead in his car May 5.
   A pathologists' report released Monday said Rose had died
accidentally of head injuries suffered when his speeding car ran
off a road near the Caribbean resort of Sosua and fell into a
ditch, flipping over several times.
   Rose, a British-born U.S. citizen who won two Tony awards, owned
a beach home just outside Sosua, about 15 miles east of Puerto
Plata.
   There was no immediate comment on the discrepancy between the
autopsy finding and the police report, but the pathologists
scheduled a news conference for later in the day.
   Pimentel Cruz identified Rose's adopted son as Domingo Antonio
Ralfe Vazquez, nicknamed ``Juan.'' Also charged was the young man's
natural father, Juan Antonio Vazquez Padilla, and another relative,
Maximo Padilla Vazquez. He did not identify the fourth man.
   The autopsy was conducted after Juan asked police to investigate
the actor's death.
   Rose won Tony awards for his Broadway roles in ``The Mystery of
Edwin Drood'' and ``My Fair Lady.''
   He was a versatile actor who was as much at home playing
Shakespeare as he was in a comedy or a musical. He preferred the
stage, but also appeared in scores of film and television
productions.
   Rose had lived in New York City since 1961.
</TEXT>
