<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Officials in two cities have opposed the
release of a former convict termed dangerous by state prison
officials and a Texas prosecutor.
   The reports about Robert E. Kleasen, 55, have produced an outcry
in Buffalo, his hometown, and in Rochester, where parole officials
first tried to place him.
