<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--NuclearTest     05-12 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Nuclear Test,0130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Test Delayed for Second Day</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAS VEGAS, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Energy Department has delayed for a
second day a major nuclear weapons test at the Nevada Test Site.
   The test was rescheduled for Friday morning.
   Thursday's delay was blamed on technical problems at
instrumentation trailers near ground zero. The test was originally
scheduled for Wednesday, but was delayed because of unfavorable
wind conditions.
   DOE spokeswoman Barbara Yoerg said workers had to go back to a
trailer area near ground zero to correct the technical problems,
and the problems could not be resolved in time to conduct the test
Thursday.
   The trailers house instruments used to record data from the
tests.
   The test, code-named Schellbourne, is the third announced shot
this year.
</TEXT>
