<TEXT>
   Actress Greer Garson Fogelson has pledged $1
million to help construct an education-conference center on the
campus of Presbyterian Hospital of Dallas, officials said Wednesday.
   The donation, made in the name of Mrs. Fogelson and her late
husband, Col. E.E. ``Buddy'' Fogelson, is intended to attract
matching contributions to the Presbyterian Healthcare Foundation.
