<HEAD>Candidate Wins Election, A Year Late</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAYLORVILLE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mary Williamson has finally won the
April 7 Pana City Council election. April 7, 1987, that is.
   A flip of a Kennedy half-dollar in a Christian County courtroom
Wednesday decided a 129-vote tie between her and Alderman Ray
Pauley.
   Ms. Williamson lost to Pauley in the Democratic primary but
waged a write-in campaign in the general election. The initial
results were a 129-to-109 victory for Pauley.
   But Ms. Williamson took those results to court, and 20 write-in
votes which had been disallowed were counted in her favor. A judge
ordered the coin flip.
   ``I've had two bottles of champagne on ice for a year, and now
we will celebrate,'' said the ecstatic victor.
   Pauley had no comment, but his wife said he won't appeal.
