<HEAD>Lucille Ball Checks Into Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Comedian Lucille Ball checked into
Cedars-Sinai Medical Center after she fell ill at home, a hospital
spokesman said Thursday.
   Miss Ball, 76, was driven to the hospital Wednesday by her
husband, Gary Morton, and walked in to admit herself, said
Cedars-Sinai spokesman Ron Wise.
   He said nothing had been diagnosed.
   ``There does not seem to be any immediate urgency,'' said Wise.
``Her personal physician decided on the side of caution and is
giving her a complete physical to determine if there is a problem.''
