<HEAD>Three Stabbed in Stockholm Clash</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: LEADS throughout with police saying fighting involved rival
Iranian factions, sted Islamic demonstrators and Israeli
supporters. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Iranian factions clashed Thursday
during a demonstration against Israel's occupation of the West Bank
and Gaza Strip, and three Iranians were stabbed, police said.
   Chief superintendent Evert Karlen said three men were arrested
on suspicion of attempted murder. One of the victims had
life-threatening wounds, police said.
   Fighting broke out after about 40 demonstrators, some carrying
pictures of Iran's revolutionary patriarch Ayatollah Ruhollah
Khomeini, gathered in Stockholm's central square to protest Israeli
policy.
   A group of anti-Khomeini activists arrived and the rival groups
shouted slogans at each other. Fighting broke out despite the
presence of police on horseback and in riot gear.
   The Swedish national news agency TT said about 100 demonstrators
gathered outside a Stockholm hospital after the clash to protest
the stabbings.
