<BYLINE>By SHIRLEY LAI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHINGCHUANKANG AIR FORCE BASE, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Chinese jetliner
with 118 people aboard was hijacked to Taiwan today by two Chinese
men seeking to defect. The aircraft later took off for China but
the hijackers remained in Taiwan, a military spokesman said.
   The Boeing 737 left Chingchuankang air force base in the central
Taiwan city of Taichung at 2:55 a.m. Friday (2:55 p.m. EDT
Thursday) for Canton in southern China after refueling, said Wang
Pao-hua, spokesman for the air base. The two hijackers asked for
political asylum in Taiwan, he said.
