that the jet was headed for the British colony of Hong Kong on
China's southeastern coast. It did not say whether the plane would
later go somewhere else.
   The hijackers carried fake guns and bombs, Taiwan Television
Station Co. said. They and the passengers and crew members had left
the Boeing after it landed in Taiwan.
   In Beijing, the official Xinhua News Agency said the plane was
hijacked to Taiwan while flying to Canton from Xiamen, in
southeastern China 136 miles across the Taiwan Strait from Taiwan.
