<HEAD>Dukakis Holds Slight Edge Going Into Colorado Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democratic presidential candidate Michael Dukakis
goes into next week's Colorado state convention with a slight lead
over Jesse Jackson, according to the latest count of convention
delegates.
   Wednesday's count of delegates to the May 21 convention in
Boulder showed 52 percent supporting Dukakis, 38 percent backing
Jackson and 10 percent uncommited or supporting another candidate.
   But unless Dukakis can pick up nearly all of those uncommitted
delegates at the state convention, he will split the 16 Colorado
national delegates with Jackson.
   ``I am committed to making that 60 percent threshold,'' said Tom
Glass, Dukakis' state campaign coordinator. ``It is very clear that
Dukakis will have a clear majority of the delegates to the state
convention, but it would be very tough ... to get a 10-6 split.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
