left four dead.
   Ms. Buck, Linda Sue Evans, and Laura Whitehorn were charged with
conspiring to wage a campaign of ``armed propaganda'' against
``imperialist rule'' by setting off bombs in the Capitol and seven
other locations in Washington and New York City.
   Susan Rosenberg, Timothy Blunk, Dr. Alan Berkman and Elizabeth
Duke were named as participants but not charged with conspiracy.
