<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
252,195 cars and trucks this week, up from last week's 249,667,
Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   Automakers produced 228,019 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 166,915 cars this
week, compared with 160,826 a week ago and 147,143 in the same week
in 1987.
   Truck production for the week was scheduled at 85,280, compared
with last week's 88,841 and last year's 80,876.
