<HEAD>London Shares Gain 15.5 Points</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices on the London Stock Exchange rose Thursday
as players crept back into the market to pick up marked-down shares
after Wednesday's rout.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was up 15.5
points, or 0.9 percent, at 1,772.3 at the close. On Wednesday, the
