<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-NationalIntergroup     05-12 0156</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-National Intergroup,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>National Intergroup Reports Loss</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   National Intergroup Inc. on Thursday reported
a loss of $30.4 million for the fourth quarter and a loss of $21.9
million for its fiscal year.
   The company said the loss for the three months ended March 31
compared with a year-earlier loss of $15.4 million.
   National Intergroup said the results included a one-time $24
million charge for the planned sale of its unprofitable aluminum
foil plant in Luxembourg.
   Sales for the latest quarter totaled $756.3 million, down from
$1.28 billion.
   National Intergroup said its loss for the year ended March 31
compared to a previous fiscal year shortfall of $45 million.
   Sales for the year slipped to $3.35 billion from $4.47 billion.
   Chairman Howard M. Love said the company's fourth-quarter
results reflected improvement in the company's day-to-day
operations.
   The company is involved in steel, aluminum and oil. It holds a
half interest in National Steel.
