<HEAD>Philadelphia Stock Exchange Elects New Chairman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John J. Wallace, the president of a
brokerage firm, has been elected chairman of the Philadelphia Stock
Exchange, the exchange's board of governors announced Thursday.
   Wallace was named acting chairman on March 22 to replace Martin
L. Longstreth Jr., who died of cancer on March 7.
   Wallace will preside over the board of governors of the
exchange. He has served as a governor of the exchange since 1974
and as vice chairman since 1984.
   Since 1983, he has been president of Park Avenue Securities.
   Wallace also is a director of the Stock Clearing Corp. of
Philadelphia, the Philadelphia Depository Trust Co., the
Philadelphia Board of Trade and the Financial Automation Corp. of
Philadelphia.
